On October 21, 2023, the Hacktoberfest event, organized by the Google Developer Students team (GDSC) under the Computer Science (CS) club at St. Mary's University graduate campus, American Corner, was a tremendous success. The primary objective of the event was to encourage open-source project contributions and featured a guest speaker, Bereket Engida. 

The event marked a collaborative effort among GDSC chapters from St. Mary's University, HiLCoE School of Computer Science and Technology, and Addis Ababa University, bringing together 38 enthusiastic students eager to explore the realm of open-source contributions.

 Hacktoberfest: a combination of 3 words Hack, October and Festival 

Hacktoberfest is a month-long celebration of open-source software when everyone is encouraged to support open-source communities.

Dear CS Club Members,

We are thrilled to announce a significant milestone for our club and St. Mary's University.  St. Mary's CS Club is proud to introduce the Google Developer Student Club (GDSC), now established at St. Mary's University. We are the 6th campus in Ethiopia to join the GDSC network!

The Google Developer Student Club is an incredible platform that offers numerous benefits, including opportunities for learning, collaboration, and innovation. As members of the CS Club, we highly encourage you to become part of the GDSC in our chapter.

To join the GDSC at St. Mary's University, follow these simple steps:

1. Visit the GDSC registration page by clicking on the following link: https://gdsc.community.dev/st-mary-university/

2. Create your GDSC profile.

3. Don't forget to click the "Join Us" button after creating your profile to officially become a part of our GDSC chapter!

This is an incredible opportunity to expand your horizons, connect with like-minded individuals, and dive deeper into the world of technology and development.

If you have any questions or need further information about GDSC, feel free to reach out to our GDSC Lead:
Minassie Ephrem
@minassie_eph

Let's embrace this new chapter together and make it a remarkable journey of learning and innovation.

Best regards,

St. Mary's University CS Club

The closing ceremony of the 8th ICT exhibition was held this morning.

✅The event was marked by a panel discussion on Cybersecurity and Its Importance. The panelists gave an overview of their projects and emphasized the importance of Cybersecurity in protecting digital assets. They talked about how cyber attacks are becoming more sophisticated and how important it is to follow best practices when it comes to protecting sensitive information. 

✅Following the panel, students spoke about their projects, the challenges they faced, and how the exhibition encouraged them to expand their works.

✅Then, certificates were given out to each member who participated in making this event possible. Dashen Bank, our sponsor, has also given gifts to students and faculty members.

✅Finally, there was a speech from the President of our university. He commended the department for hosting such a wonderful exhibition and highlighted the administration's commitment in supporting similar ICT activities.

All in all, we can confidently say that this year's ICT exhibition has been a resounding achievement. Over the past few days, the event has provided a platform for students to network, share ideas and collaborate on projects.

We want to express our heartfelt gratitude to our school, department, advisors, and faculty members who worked tirelessly to ensure everything went successfully.

To all students 
You are invited to attend the closing ceremony of ICT Exhibition tomorrow May 31/2023 starting from 3:00 local time at undergraduate campus multi-purpose hall. Please, be there on time.
Share it with your class groups.
Day 2 of #ICT_Exhibition

The exhibition kicked off by the key note speech of the president. Then, other respected guests who came from our own university, INSA and other well known companies made speeches sharing their experiences and insights. Following the remarkable speech of our Department head - Mr. Habte, the exhibition was officially opened.

Afterwards, the guests were taken around to see various projects that were presented at the event. There were jaw dropping projects targeting different industries such as agriculture, healthcare, education, communication and many more. 

Overall, the event has provided a platform for innovators to showcase their work and get feedback form experts in their respective fields. It is also an opportunity for guests to learn about various technologies and innovations that are shaping our world today.

The exhibition will stay for the next two consecutive days and it's open for anyone interested specially for computer science students. You can visit all the awesome projects at the Multipurpose Hall, Undergraduate Campus. 

Don't Miss Out!
'Day 1' of the 8th #ICT_Exhibition held on 29th of May was a huge success!

Welcome to our Telegram channel, the virtual hub for the nerdiest and most exciting happenings of our college's Computer Science Club!

Are you a tech enthusiast, a coding addict, or simply curious about the world of computer science? Look no further! Our community is dedicated to fostering a passion for all things tech-related.

Join us for engaging discussions, lively debates, and insightful presentations on the latest trends and developments in the industry. From hackathons to coding challenges, we offer a wide range of activities and events to suit every level of expertise and interest.

So whether you're a seasoned pro or just getting started on your coding journey, come along for the ride and discover what makes our club a unique and dynamic community of like-minded individuals. See you on the other side of the screen!
